    <h2> Install environment </h2>
        
        The installation of the environment is done via the <a href="https://docs.docker.com/engine/install/"> docker tool </a>. Therefore, be sure to have already installed the Docker tool on your system. 
        
        <ul role="list">
        
        <li> The first step is to download the docker image at:  <a href="https://github.com/JammingWiFiNs3/DockerFileJammerNS.git"> image </a> </li>

        <li> Then build the image : </li>
        <pre> <code class=""> docker build -t "jammer" . </code></pre>

        <blockquote>
            <p>Attention, do not forget the dot at the end of the command.</p>
            <p> This will take a few minutes, please wait </p>
        </blockquote>

        <li>Finaly, run the image </li>

       <pre> <code class=""> docker run -it "jammer" </code></pre>

        </ul>

      <h2> Modify the containt of jamming module </h2>
